\f3\b\fs48 \cf2 \cb3 How to Create Style Variations in WordPress Themes?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 Style variations are alternate design configurations created by adding theme.json files to a theme\'92s styles directory. Each variation file defines a title and slug, then overrides or extends the base theme\'92s settings and styles values. These variations inherit the theme\'92s core templates, layout structure, and functional behavior, changing only the design layer\'97such as color palettes, typography rules, spacing scales, and other visual parameters.\cb1 \
\cb3 When present, WordPress detects variation files and displays them in the Global Styles panel as selectable design options. Because they modify only settings and styles, variations operate strictly as design-layer overrides without altering templates, blocks, or site structure.\cb1 \
\cb3 Example variation file:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 \{\
  "title": "Modern Light",\
  "slug": "modern-light",\
  "settings": \{\},\
  "styles": \{\}\
\}
\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 File location:\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f4\fs20\fsmilli10240 \cf6 \cb7 /wp-content/themes/your-theme/styles/modern-light.json
\fs25\fsmilli12800 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa398\partightenfactor0

